{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"aca6f04d-2888-4289-8e10-848d060abdcf","content":"There are no files in the working directory, so I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` root element pointing to your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **key change** is `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the root element. This tells the XAML compiler the type of the `BindingContext`, so every `{Binding ...}` beneath it is validated and compiled.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\nBy default, `x:DataType` generates compiled bindings but **warnings** for invalid paths may be suppressed. To turn them into **build errors**, add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat binding-related warnings as errors -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045;XC0022;XC0023</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `XC0045` | Property not found on the specified `x:DataType` |\n| `XC0022` | No matching property/method for binding |\n| `XC0023` | Binding path type mismatch |\n\nNow if you typo a property name (e.g. `{Binding Themee}`), the build will **fail** instead of silently falling back to reflection at runtime.\n\n### One gotcha\n\nIf a subtree binds to a different type (e.g. inside a `DataTemplate`), set `x:DataType` on that element too. To opt out of compiled bindings for a specific binding (e.g. a relative source), use `x:DataType=\"\"` locally.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"016f99c9-86ac-4e95-b103-bc9140d78e52","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. The user is asking about a conceptual task — converting a .NET MAUI page to use compiled bindings. They don't actually have the files in the working directory. Let me provide them with the guidance they need.\n\nLet me give a clear, concise answer about how to convert to compiled bindings and catch errors at build time.","outputTokens":803},"id":"2749ad91-1bc0-433b-810b-b4e03d7cf857","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:21:52.877Z","parentId":"df53005a-88b4-4bb3-bc14-43a34d4902f6"}
